body:
@FlorianHockmann, thank you for this excellent driver, it's what allows us to get the most out of Cosmos.  If this wasn't reality, I would have pushed off the use of a graph DB, even though it's the right fit for my use case.

Yes, conceptually, whatever I am doing externally, we can realize internally, without exposure to the consumer, other than the raising of an error.

If you could provide guidance as to which code you would like modified, I would be happy to help out.

@FlorianHockmann great question.  yes, i saw this in TryGetAvailableConnection, and planned to follow this, but i had PROD issues on some other threads, so i put a band-aid, notified you via PR, and moved on. now that i see the Jira link, i will communicate there.  

without digging too deeply, i see that HasOpenConnection checks both IsOpen and _connectionState, but ConnectionPool only checks IsOpen.  this allows Submit to BeginSendingMessages. and following this down, the SendMessageAsync call may snag on a dead connection, which still returns true for IsOpen, but its state may not be correct.  now that i have some breathing room from the PROD issues, i will try to reproduce this to be able to tell you the exact line where this manifests.  then i will try to sign up for the jira group and add it as an issue.

@jorgebay looking forward to be able to contribute
